-- Swiss Franc Falls After Finance Minister Says Considering Capital Controls
-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r o w n
-- 2011-12-21T16:20:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/swiss-franc-falls-after-finance-minister-says-considering-capital-controls.html
The franc fell against the euro and
the dollar after Finance Minister Eveline Widmer-Schlumpf said a
panel is considering measures, including capital controls and
negative  interest rates , to weaken the Swiss currency.  The franc fell 0.3 percent to 1.2218 per euro at 4:17 p.m.
London time, and 0.6 percent to 93.77 centimes per dollar.  Widmer-Schlumpf was speaking at a hearing in the Swiss
